text.tspan: Kilo Nalu Shore Station Linux System
Ocean and Atmospheric data measurement instruments stream data in realtime varying rates (1sec, 5sec, 1min, 15min, 1day etc.) into the ring buffers. They are processed by sink
software into a data archive, and further processed into 15min summary plots avaiable online. The data are replicated in realtime to the campus system, with independent replication
of the data archive via rsync.
U. Hawaii HIG Campus Linux System
